11:10 AM ADA calls cases: 22CF85, 22CM51 and states appearances. Defendant Levi J Lukes in court.  Attorney Luke J Fischer Sr. in court for Levi J Lukes.  Attorney Mark T. Fuhr in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Fischer states his client will be waiving the Preliminary hearing in case 22CF85 and that the signed form has been filed. Court questions the defendant on waiver. Defendant gives responses. Preliminary Hearing waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. ADA Fuhr states they do not have an Information filed at this time. Court questions Attorney Fischer on moving to arraignment. Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts. Attorney Fischer requests a Motion hearing for 60 days out. Status hearing on September 15, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

**No Contact includes: Going to or remaining in any place the individual resides, is employed at, attends school at, or any public location the individual is temporarily located. Contact through means of telephone. Electronic devices, Social media, email, regular mail, or a 3rd party individual is prohibited. The only exception to this order is contact through your attorney or law enforcement in appropriate circumstances.
